{"author":{"id":"2329d242a564d858d1460ecfa8faffbd4bbf14caa989b5b8c6fcd76a16aedb80"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1660142947,"nonce":"dQHuFHAUigw2EbY9viCTs2eJKr8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s5IKxk3","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4651#issuecomment-1210784055"},"message":"Hi @pimarin - yes, I don't think refseq_masher has an option for updating its database.\n\nAs to a data manager: this is a special kind of tool that updates a \"data table\". These tools are not run by users but rather by the Galaxy server admin. Unfortunately there are not very good docs for writing them but there are several examples in the [data_managers](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/tree/master/data_managers) section of this Github repository. I don't think we should wait till a data manager can be built to support referenceseeker though. It is something useful to have for the future.\n\nThe referenceseeker tool expects the database to be in a directory, unpacked from the .tar.gz files that they provide. There is no easy way to provide a directory as a dataset in Galaxy, so the user would have to, I think, put the .tar.gz for the database in their history and then the tool would have to unpack it before using it. This is resource intensive but I don't see another way to write a wrapper right now. Maybe others have other suggestions.","files":null}]}